dc_title_s: Map of the United States road from Ohio to Detroit as lately located by Messrs. A. Edwards, S. Vance and Philu E. Judd (the last of whom died before the survey was completed), commissioners appointed by the president of the U.S. agreeable to act of Congress; drawn by J. Farmer of Detroit, 1825.
dc_description_s: Prime meridian: Washington. Oriented with north toward the upper right. 1 map: photocopy; 21 x 79 cm
